Treatment Options
Treatment depends on the severity of the condition:
Lifestyle Changes:
Increase dietary fiber intake with fruits, vegetables, and whole grains.
Stay hydrated by drinking plenty of water.
Avoid straining during bowel movements.
Incorporate regular exercise to improve blood circulation.
Home Remedies:
Warm sitz baths can soothe irritation.
Over-the-counter creams and ointments help reduce inflammation and discomfort.
Medical Interventions:
Non-surgical treatments: Rubber band ligation, sclerotherapy, or infrared coagulation may be used for mild to moderate cases.
Surgical options: In severe cases, hemorrhoidectomy or stapled hemorrhoidopexy may be recommended.

Prevention
Preventing piles is easier than treating them. Adopt a healthy lifestyle with a fiber-rich diet, regular exercise, and good bowel habits. Avoid sitting for prolonged periods, and manage conditions like constipation promptly.
